=August 2012}}\n\n==Rowing==\n{{main|Rowing at the 1928 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Empty section|date=August 2012}}\n\n==Wrestling==\n{{main|Wrestling at the 1928 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Empty section|date=August 2012}}\n\n==References==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20060622162855/http://www.la84foundation.org/5va/reports_frmst.htm Official Olympic Reports]\n*[http://www.olympic.org/uk/athletes/results/search_r_uk.asp International Olympic Committee results database]\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{country at games navbox|Japan|Olympics}}\n{{Nations at the 1928 Summer Olympics}}\n\n[[Category:Nations at the 1928 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Japan at the Summer Olympics by year|1928]]\n[[Category:1928 in Japanese sport|Summer Olympics]]\n", "text_old": "{{infobox country at games\n| NOC = JPN\n| NOCname = [[Japanese Olympic Committee]]\n| games = Summer Olympics\n| year = 2021\n| flagcaption = \n| oldcode = \n| website = {{url|www.joc.or.jp }}&nbsp;{{in lang|ja|en}}\n| location = [[Amsterdam]]\n| competitors = 43\n| sports = \n| flagbearer = Yonetaro Nakazawa\n| rank = 15\n| gold = 2\n| silver = 2\n| bronze = 1\n| officials = \n| appearances = auto\n| app_begin_year = 1912\n| app_end_year = \n| summerappearances = \n| winterappearances = \n| seealso = \n}}\nThe '''[[Empire of Japan]]''' competed at the '''[[1928 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Amsterdam]], [[Netherlands]].\n\n==Background==\nThe Japan Amateur Athletic Federation (''Nihon Rikujo Kyogi Renmei''), founded in 1925, officially took over sponsorship of the Japanese Olympic team from the Japan Amateur Athletic Association in 1928. Japanese government sponsorship of the Olympic effort continued, both financially, and through expansion of the annual Meiji Shrine Games to include a wider variety of sports, including archery, basketball, field hockey, rowing, table tennis,  volleyball and equestrian sports.<ref>Guttman, Allen. ''Japanese Sports: A History'' (University of Hawaii Press, 2001), p. 119-120.</ref>\n\nThe games became the qualifying event for the Japanese Olympic team, which now for the first time included a woman ([[Kinue Hitomi]]). For the 1928 Olympics, Japan fielded 43 athletes.\n\n==Medalists==\n{{col-begin}}\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|- \n! Medal \n! Name\n! Sport \n! Event \n|-    \n| {{gold medal}} || {{sortname|Mikio|Oda}} || [[Athletics at the 1928 Summer Olympics|Athletics]] || [[Athletics at the 1928 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's triple jump|Men's triple jump]]\n|-    \n| {{gold medal}} || {{sortname|Yoshiyuki|Tsuruta}} || [[Swimming at the 1928 Summer Olympics|Swimming]] || [[Swimming at the 1928 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 200 metre breaststroke|Men's 200 m breaststroke]]\n|-    \n| {{silver medal}} || {{sortname|Kinue|Hitomi}} || [[Athletics at the 1928 Summer Olympics|Athletics]] || [[Athletics at the 1928 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 800 metres|Women's 800 m]]\n|-    \n| {{silver medal}} || {{sortname|Hiroshi|Yoneyama}}, [[Nobuo Arai]], [[Tokuhei Sada]] and [[Katsuo Takaishi]] || [[Swimming at the 1928 Summer Olympics|Swimming]] || [[Swimming at the 1928 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 4 \u00d7 200 metre freestyle relay|Men's 4 \u00d7 200 m freestyle relay]]\n|-    \n| {{bronze medal}} || {{sortname|Katsuo|Takaishi}} || [[Swimming at the 1928 Summer Olympics|Swimming]] || [[Swimming at the 1928 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 100 metre freestyle|Men's 100 m freestyle]]\n|}\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|\n\n{{Clear}}\n{|\n|-\n|\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%; float:right\"\n!colspan=5|'''Medals by sport'''\n|- align=center\n|'''Sport'''\n!bgcolor=#f7f6a8|{{gold01}}\n!bgcolor=#dce5e5|{{silver02}}\n!bgcolor=#ffdab9|{{bronze03}}\n!'''Total'''\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Swimming at the 1928 Summer Olympics|Swimming]]||bgcolor=#f7f6a8|1||bgcolor=#dce5e5|1||bgcolor=#ffdab9|1||3\n|- align=center\n|align=left|[[Athletics at the 1928 Summer Olympics|Athletics]]||bgcolor=#f7f6a8|1||bgcolor=#dce5e5|1